## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> 1. **What is SideStore's actual process name on your device?** Run `ps aux | grep -i side` to find it. It could be `SideStore`, `AltStore`, or the executable name from the bundle.
> 2. **Do you want to modify SideStore's source code** to add the `sidestore://refresh` URL handler? Or do you prefer the approach that just opens/foregrounds SideStore (which triggers `AppManager.shared.update()` but not a full refresh)?
> 3. **Are you running from lara or darksword directly?** This determines which API style (ObjC C-functions vs Swift RemoteCall class) we use.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Testing
1. Build and deploy darksword/lara with the new refresh function
2. Run the exploit to get KRW
3. Initialize RemoteCall on SpringBoard
4. Call the refresh function
5. Verify SideStore opens and begins refreshing apps (check SideStore's logs/UI)
